Controversial Kenya Films and Classification Board Chief executive officer Ezekiel Mutua has been sent on terminal leave following a directive from ICT cabinet secretary Joe Mucheru. The CEO, who has been at the helm of the content regulatory organ for 6 years now had earlier stated that he was still in office before his replacement was quickly announced on Friday. KTN's Timothy Otieno reports on an end to a tenure filled with controversy for man love and loathed in equal measure.